documentation.text:
@dev This library is used by {Agora} and {Delegation} contracts for law project elaboration. It provides facilities for law project creation, propositions submission, Law execution... 
 Every citizen can submit one or more proposal for the function call corpus of the law project. Proposals are stored in a Proposal Tree where each proposal can reuse function calls of its parent proposal.
 When a citizen wants to submit a proposal via the Add_Proposal function, he has to pay tokens for each new function call but function calls that come from the parent proposal are free. Hence, citizens can spare tokens by reusing already proposed function call. 
 This is an incentive for citizens to avoid duplicate or unnecessary function call. 
 The tree structure increases the readability of the proposal corpus as similar proposal would have the same parents.
 Once a citizen has submitted a proposal, he still has the possibility to insert new function call to it via the Add_Item function.

devdoc.details: This library is used by {Agora} and {Delegation} contracts for law project elaboration. It provides facilities for law project creation, propositions submission, Law execution...  Every citizen can submit one or more proposal for the function call corpus of the law project. Proposals are stored in a Proposal Tree where each proposal can reuse function calls of its parent proposal. When a citizen wants to submit a proposal via the Add_Proposal function, he has to pay tokens for each new function call but function calls that come from the parent proposal are free. Hence, citizens can spare tokens by reusing already proposed function call.  This is an incentive for citizens to avoid duplicate or unnecessary function call.  The tree structure increases the readability of the proposal corpus as similar proposal would have the same parents. Once a citizen has submitted a proposal, he still has the possibility to insert new function call to it via the Add_Item function.

Add_Corpus_Proposal(Initiative_Legislati.details: In the Parent_Proposals_Reuse and New_Function_Call arrays elements are ordered in the order in which function call will be executed at the execution time.  Indexes corresponding to "New_Function_Call" function call elements are merged with "Parent_Proposals_Reuse" in order to create a list of all the functions calls ("Function_Calls" field of "Corpus_Proposal" struct) of the new proposal.   ex: Parent_Proposals_Reuse= [3,0,1,5,0];  New_Function_Call=[function_call1, function_call2, function_call3]  =>   [3, IndexOf(function_call1), 1,5,IndexOf(function_call2)];     function_call3 is ignored note: Index values correspond to the indexes in the "All_Proposed_Function_Calls" array of the "Law_Project" struct.   The function doesn't set "Author" field of Corpus_Proposal struct because of "stack too deep" error. Hence, this task have to be done by the caller function.

params.Description: Text explaining the goals of the proposal. It can be used for example to justify the benefit of new added function call. If this parameter is null, it means that the description of this new proposal is the same as the description of the law project.
params.New_Function_Call: Array of bytes corresponding to new functions calls that are specific to the new proposal.
params.Parent: Parent proposal of the new proposal
params.Parent_Proposals_Reuse: List of parent's function call that are going to be reused in the new proposal. It's an array containing the indexes of the Parent function calls. If an element of the array is null, it means that the corresponding spot will be occupied by a new function call.

Add_Item_Proposal(Initiative_Legislative.details: The function can be called to add function calls to a proposition that he has already created (He have to be the author of the proposition).

params.Indexs: array of Proposition's function call list indexs to inser new function call (contained in {New_Items}) to. {New_Items} and {Indexs} have the same length.
params.New_Items: Array of new function calls to add to the Proposition.
params.Project_Law: Id of the law project the caller wants to add a proposition to. The Id is obtained by hashing the Title with the Description of the law project.
params.author: Author of the proposition we want to add new functions calls to.

Add_Law_Project(Initiative_Legislative_L.details: It's advised to enter Title and Description parameters as hash.

params.Description: Text explaining the spirit and generals goals of the law project. Can be an hash.
params.Title: title of the new law project. Can be an hash.

Execute_Winning_Proposal(Initiative_Legi.details: This function execute all function calls of the winning proposal of law project.

params.num_function_call_ToExecute: Number of function calls to execute.
params.register_address: Address of the register contract whose register functions would be called by winning proposition's function calls.

Get_FunctionCall_List(Initiative_Legisla.details: Get the list of all function calls that have been submitted in a law project (no matter in which proposal).

Get_Law_Project_Results(Initiative_Legis.details: Get results of a law project. It returns the id of the winning proposal and an array of receipts returned by winning proposal's function calls.

Get_Proposal_FunctionCall_List(Initiativ.details: Get the list of function calls of a Proposal.

Get_Proposal_Infos(Initiative_Legislativ.details: Get global informations about a law project's proposal. It return the Proposal's description, the list of proposal children, the number of function calls, the parent proposal and author.

Add_Corpus_Proposal(Initiative_Legislati.notice: Add a new proposal to the Proposals tree of the current law project. This proposal is composed both by functions call (i.e. bytes corresponding to the "data" field in a low level call) coming from it's parent proposal and by new functions call that are specific to the new created proposal.
